    "Clearly a ∼ B a ′ if and only if a and a ′ are BGisomorphic (Definition 3.2.7).",
    "It is easily checked that for a ∼ B a ′ and b ∼ B b ′ one has bpol •/b (a, b) = bpol •/b (a ′, b ′) We define a new category BPOL • the objects of which are equivalence classes of ∼ B and where a morphism of codomain ȧ and codomain ḃ is any element of bpol •/b, in symbols: BPOL • ( ȧ, ḃ) = bpol •/b (a, b).)",
    "The effective p-site associated with a is the p-site a * ∶= ( (I, A *, (A i))).",
    "It is characterized by the parting function π a * = π a|A *.",
    "Clearly κ a * = κ a ∖ {∅} and σ a * = σ a."
